\begin{align*}
  \psi(x) &= \sqrt{\frac{2}{a}}\sin\left(\frac{\pi x}{a}\right) \\
  P(0 \leq x \leq a/2) &= \int_0^{a/2} \psi(x)\,\mathrm{d}x \\
  &= \int_0^{a/2} \sqrt{\frac{2}{a}}\sin\left(\frac{\pi x}{a}\right)\,\mathrm{d}x \\
  &= \left[-\sqrt{\frac{2}{a}}\frac{a}{\pi}\cos\left(\frac{\pi x}{a}\right)\right]_0^{a/2} \\
  &= \frac{2}{\pi} - \sqrt{\frac{2}{a}}\frac{a}{\pi} \\
  &= \frac{2}{\pi} - \frac{\sqrt{2a}}{\pi}
\end{align*}
Is this correct?


